From bb5d1f637b5dff647ae56c55014d1b9535f60968 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 15:17:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add unified unit activity timeline (audit log)

New ActivityLog model + module: one unit-scoped, plain-language event
feed instead of scattered signals (task.completedAt, unit comments,
etc.) that each only tell part of the story. Logged automatically at
every meaningful business event, not manually per-page:

- Unit created
- Engineering stage advanced
- Planner assigned parts and released to Production Manager
- Manager released to Fabrication
- Manufacturing started (Fabrication's Start Entire Unit)
- Assembly build started (with team name)
- Task completed (both direct completion and verify-then-complete)
- Delay/blocker comments (only isDelay=true ones - regular comments
  already have their own visible list, no need to duplicate them)
- Vendor part received (both at creation and when flipped to received
  later - date-only edits are NOT logged, that would flood the
  timeline with noise every time an arrival date gets adjusted)
- Unit blocked/unblocked, with the hold reason

Logging never blocks or fails the real operation it's attached to -
ActivityLogService.log() catches and swallows its own errors (logged
to console) rather than letting a logging problem turn an unrelated
write into a 500.

New GET /units/:id/activity endpoint, and a timeline card on the unit
detail page showing every entry with who/when, right below Comments.
Reuses the existing WebSocket-driven query invalidation for live
updates - React Query invalidates by key prefix, so the existing
['unit', id] invalidations already cover the ['unit', id, 'activity']
query without any new wiring.

This directly enables item 2 from an earlier request in this session
("manager should see who confirmed a process completed and at what
time") with a real, permanent record instead of a one-off field.
